I use the following commands:

mov
jump
jnz
ceq
mult

I have the following registers:

R0 n+1
R1 n-1, n-2, ..., 1
R2 index of current element
R3 current element address
R4 current element
R5 temp
R6 pair element address 
R7 pair element 

The first element of matrix is writen in 0x0 address of Memory
The matrix size is writen in ax0 address of Memory
I need to reverse the matrix.

The program is:

move R0, *ax0 // n
move R1, R0 // 
add R1, -1 // n-1
move R2, R1 // n-1
add R0, 1 // n+1
move R3, 0x0 //
loop: 
	ceq R2, 0
	jnz loop1	
	add R3, 1    // current element address
	move R4, *R3 // current element 
	move R5, R4 // save current element in temp
	move R6, R3
	add R6, R0 // address of the pair element
	move R3, *R6 // swap
	move R7, R5 // swap
	move *R3, R4 // change in Memory
	move *R6, R7 // change in Memory
	add R2, -1
	jump loop 
loop1:
	ceq R1, 0
	jnz exit
	add R1, -1
	jump loop
exit:
	exit

